Text.string: Boots on the ground, Rhys.
Landed, Rhys.
I've arrived, Rhys.
Here, boyo. Nice view!
Whoa, that actually worked? I mean, of course that worked—and no death-spheres in sight!
Never mind. According to Zer0's intel, your Vault Key Fragment is powering the laser. We just gotta find the control room. Head to the main gate. No death spheres.
I'm in. Bypassing security protocols now. I said now! Now! Now, you stupid... oh no...
Rhys, is that you? Welcome! So, once we make your unconditional surrender nice and official, you and I are gonna party on the Zanara. That's my pleasure yacht.
Oh, uh, h-hey. Yeah, uh, see, the, uh... the whole laser thing, well, um. It's just making it hard for my employees to work down here. It's really starting to kill morale a little bit.
Who cares about them? I'm doing this for us. The people who matter. The executives. But you're ruining it, Rhys. You're ruining it by trying to defend yourself.
Security! Kill the Vault Hunter.
Target located. Laser fire in three, two, one...
Hey, cult weirdos. Vault Hunters incoming. Kill them.
So, I figured out how to hack Katagawa's laser! And the control room is just up ahead!
Nah, that one's full of ratch turds.
Mm, too big. Not my style.
Oh, that is perfect! It just screams Rhys! “Rhys!” Use the Viper Drive.
I'm in! Ooh, anti-grav propulsion. Cushy. Oh, uh, the voice sounds good too, right? Not, um... changed in any way?
So for the record, this is not a probe, do NOT call me “Rhys-probe” or whatever.
Call me... Rhys-sphere! Wow, that's, that's actually, that's pretty tough to say.||“Rhys-sphere”.||“Rhys-sphe—”||Ach, I just bit my tongue. Call me... Rhys-ball!
Time to stop that laser and get your Vault Key fragment! For Atlas!
Ball scan complete! That does not sound right. This way to the control room!

Attention, loyal Maliwan personnel. Anyone who brings me a dead Vault Hunter will receive a two-hour pass to the Zanara, currently in orbit and featuring a twenty-five cheese nacho fountain, round-the-clock skag-oil massages, and privacy booths with our service bots, no questions asked.
Laser firing in three, two, one...
Recharge sequence initiating.

That's it! If we don't stop Katagawa's laser, he's gonna turn Atlas HQ into a duplex. And CEOs do not live in duplexes! Maybe Tediore's CEO does... I mean, those guns are garbage with a trigger, heh-heh, right? Burn!||I'm still sad about Fran's... but the fate of the entire planet is at stake! We can mourn later.

Attention. I'm now offering a VIP pass to the Zanara, where you can enjoy freshly-rolled Narian cigars, a dip in our fondue hot tub, and skyscraper shrimp cocktails. Price of admission is one Vault Hunter that just won't die.
So here's the plan. We storm the control room, take the Vault Key fragment, and shut down the laser. Cool? Cool! High fives. I can't do that.

Attention, Maliwan personnel. After we adopt Atlas into our family and end this war, be sure to RSVP to the victory party on the Zanara, featuring four cat cafes, all the grass-fed Saurian steaks you can cram in your peasant maws, and a zero-G swimming pool. Price of admission, the Vault Hunter's head.
You'll need to secure the control room. Then I'll hack the laser.
Oooh, Digby Vermouth! Classic!
For Atlas! And for Rhys-ball!
Okay, now time for ol' Rhys-ball to hack the laser. Before we shut it down, let's break a few of Katagawa's toys, huh? Starting with his stupid pleasure yacht, “the Zanara.”
New coordinates accepted. Familial target identified. Zanara. Class-2F pleasure yacht. Familial lock overridden. Firing sequence initiated.
Override firing sequence immediately! Security! DO SOMETHING!
I've almost got a lock on the Zanara. Defend me while I finish the hack!
Rhys. Listen. Real talk. Someone stronger was going to take over Atlas. If it wasn't Maliwan, it would've been Jakobs or Vladof or even Tediore for crying out loud.
I tried to make this comfortable for you, Rhys. True, I killed a lot of your employees. Like, “a lot” a lot. But that is just how business is done.
Vault Hunter! Fire the laser!
Laser firing in three, two, one...
Sayonara, Zanara!
Oh-ho-ho-HO! Shit! That, that was amazing! Eat my big ball, Katagawa!
Ghaaagagahaagahhhh!
Ah, come on! I mean, what's a—what's a little destruction of personal property between corporate takeover buddies?
There it is!
Rhys-ball! No!
Yes—yes! It's... it's finally over. You did it! Grab the fragment!
Thanks! But let's just take a moment to remember the fallen. Rest in peace, Rhys-ball. Rest in peace.
Nice murdering! I'll find you a way in. Pop a Viper Drive into that console so I can hack security and locate the fragment.
Uh oh, looks like there's security up ahead—you take care of them. I will make sure they can't call for back-up.
Viper Drive. When your hacking skills need some BITE. Viper Drive, by Atlas.
The main elevator leads right down to the laser. We'll be in and out so fast, Katagawa won't know what hit him!
Now call the elevator. It'll take you right down to the laser!
Boo-ya! And that's only half-power. If you don't surrender soon, Rhys, I'm gonna slice you in half!
Yo, COV! Bring me a Vault Hunter head. I'm gonna hollow it out and use it for a coozy while I'm partyin' on the Zanara.
Ugh, what are you inept apes doing? Kill the Vault Hunter!
Viper Drive. When you've got pink eye and can't open your front door with a retinal scan... we'll be there. Atlas. State-of-the-art.
Viper Drive: when you just gotta know what your neighbors are saying about you. By Atlas: state of the art.
Ugh... why didn't I pick a death-sphere? This pleasure-sphere is useless! Oh, tell you what. I'll play some music to get you in the killing mood.
I hope Rhys knows what he's doing. Lilith says he's one of us, but... you can't trust a man with a mustache. That's just science.
Enter the base and pop a Viper Drive into the security console. Then I will hack in and locate the laser control room.
Wait a sec... Rhys, why ARE there Vault Hunters here? Tell me you weren't trying to take out my laser. It's my FAVORITE LASER, Rhys.
Hold them off! I can fix this!
Damn it! He locked down the elevator. Let's see... oh, hell yeah! Some spy stuff! Head through those ventilation ducts.
Once they're dead, you can eat the rest, make 'em into puppets, whatever. Just kill them already!

Dammit! Ugh—if I were down there, I would totally hack that door. Like a cool guy. Oooh! Oh! Wait, wait, wait! I got an idea. I can remote-control one of those admittedly sweet spheres and join you! Pick one out for me.

Don't be fooled, Rhys. Your employees aren't like us. They'd stab you in the back for an extra day off. If I stab you, Rhys, you better believe it'll be right in the chest. Because that's what bros do!
Okay, one sec.
I'd always wondered at the sheer size of these Vault Key fragments. Perhaps the Eridians were larger than us. Or stronger. I shall examine this new fragment in private.
All I needed to hear. We're on it.
Pop in a Viper Drive! Atlas: it's state-of-the-art.
Ah, crap. This is a pleasure-sphere, not a death-sphere. I've got lubricant, music protocols, and an ambient light show, so... you're gonna have to clear out those troops, Vault Hunter.
Nice one! This way!
Ah, damn it! Katagawa set up a firewall. We've gotta destroy the servers. This way!
I'll open the door!
Ah, uh, actually, I'll stay here. You destroy the servers and come back out.
Nice one! Now come back out.
To the laser control room!
That's the second piece of the Vault Key! Bring it to me aboard Sanctuary.
Bring the Key fragment to me in the lab, Vault Hunter.
Now we're talking! Yay, allies! Rhys out.
You may leave now.
Oh, by the way—be careful with this low gravity. Might take some... getting used to.
Go down there and help Rhys with his laser issue, Vault Hunter.
It's Vault-o-clock, baby! Meet me at... launchpad 7.

Hey! You got yourself a fragment! Making your own Vault Key? That's fun. You know what we've been making? An ever-hungry tide of ravenous followers sweeping over the galaxy committing super-murder in our name! Just a thought: if you wanna keep up, ya might spend more time recruiting and less time polishing your gun.
I'm not sure anyone calls me that anymore.
Oh, look—a thousand more bandits pledged their lives to me while we were chatting. Good thing, too—I am starving!
Hey, you made it! My ship's right there. State-of-the-art Atlas cloaking, baby. This way!
Oh, Vault Hunter, heh. Didn't see ya there. Thanks for listening... in. Here, from your old pal Rhys.
Ghh... KATAGAWA!
Damn. You kill real good. Real good!
Rhys, buddy! Given that unconditional surrender any more thought? Or do you need another love slap from your old pal Laser-roid to change your mind?
I'd die before I hand over Atlas to that corporate ass-hat. New plan, new plan. We steal a Maliwan shuttle with security protocols! Here, take this.
Hell yeah! Quick question—is that mustache authorized?
Of course. Uh... your mustache is... very distracting.
Yes. But what's going on with your face-plumage? Is it to attract a mate? Or scare away predators?
Already doin' it in my mind! And the mustache, boyo. Bet it's got a story...
Now let's go stop that laser!
Focus. Just—just find yourself a Maliwan shuttle and pop in a Viper Drive! I will do the rest!
Security? KILL THE FREAKING VAULT HUNTER!
So, uh, the Viper Drive is Atlas state-of-the-art remote hacking. Now we'll use that baby to steal a Maliwan shuttle. You in?
Okay. Time to try out the Viper Drive! So. Pop it into that console.
Just gotta get in somewhere you're not wanted? Viper Drive, by Atlas. It's state-of-the-art.
Yes! We're in!
Nice shooting!
Ah, crap. No, no, no, no. Don't worry, I'll fix this. One sec.
You gotta offer something my family actually wants, Katagawa.
Kill the Vault Thief, and you'll earn a place right next to me when we open the Great Vault!
Not so fast, Vault Thief. Got some fam who'd LOVE to eat ya!
Oh crap, head's up!
Heya, Vault Hunter. Viper Drive, state-of-the-art garbage. Now die, please!
Yo Rhys, are those death-spheres?
Hey Rhys, are THOSE death-spheres?
Rhys—are THOSE death-spheres?
Rhys, fella—are those death-spheres?
Oh, no. I mean, y-yeah—watch out!
Password “beefstank” accepted. Your shuttle is waiting.
Ha-hah! Rhys comes through. High-fives? Anybody? Okay, okay! Hey, uh... let me know when you're there!
Lilith! Long time. So... how are things?
I dunno. You sound like you.
Acha, who cares? Get it together.
Focus, Rhys. Focus.
Your voice is like a nervous angel.
The fragment!
So what is this all about, Lilith? Why is Maliwan on Athenas? Our Key fragment has been a secret for generations. How did they find out about it now?

I'm not sure. But the Calypsos seem to know more about the Vaults than any of us, even Tannis. They knew about the Vault Map; maybe they told Maliwan to invade Athenas. They say they're after something called the Great Vault, and the Vault on Promethea must be part of their plan. We have to get there first.
We'll see about that. So... you, uh, find the map?
Found, then stolen. Tyreen has it.
That's called strategy, bitch.
No... no, no, no, no-no-no-no-no-no-NO! Agwhwh... gahhh!
Oh, heh-heh, thanks. Think I'm gettin' the hang of this.
Over here! Follow Rhys-ball!
Eat it, thrusters!

So Maliwan has that laser on lockdown. There's no way your drop pod would get through security. Buuut... I've got a state-of-the-art Atlas-brand ship with cloaking! So, the plan is to fly up to the Orbital Platform and take out that laser before Katagawa knows what hit him.
Tch, screw you!
When you're ready, just swing by with the paperwork. Can't wait to absorb Atlas into the Maliwan family! Oh, and you can bring Zer0! I'll bet he's interested.
Dammit! That was where I get my bi-weekly mustache trim! KATAGAWA!
Uh... “death-spheres”?
Uh—what's a death-sphere?
Did you say... “death-spheres”?
Death-spheres, eh?
That is the Zanara, Katagawa's pleasure yacht. Rumor is he invited his siblings on board for a party and then murdered them. That's how he became head of Mergers & Acquisitions at Maliwan.
Okay, fragment's not far. I'm gonna open that gate. There's reinforcements on the other side, so find some cover and ambush them!
Ah, here they come!
They lead straight into the maintenance area!
All right! Head through maintenance! I might have found a way into the laser control room.
Wow. Nice mustache.
Stupid Katagawa. I totally coulda held him off... Then he allied with the stupid Children of the Vault. Those cultists have been working themselves to death. I can't compete with free labor!
Oh Rhys, I know your stupid Vault Hunters are skulking about. Better sign those surrender papers, buddy. Otherwise...
Noooo, that was my favorite bagel place! Katagawa, you MONSTER!
Oh, Rhys? Buddy. I still haven't received those surrender papers. Let's see, what should I target next? How about your favorite theme park?
Laser firing in three bananas, two bananas, one banana...
No—not Lazy River Land. Anything but Lazy River Land!
NOOOO! Ghghgh, damn it!
Laser recharge sequence initiated.
Don't worry, Rhys. We've got an anti-grav infinity lazy river on the Zanara. Price of admission... Atlas.
Arrrrgh! We've got to find a way to disable that laser!

Thanks! It's a siege mustache. Listen, I'm gonna have to cash in that allies card. Katagawa's got an asteroid-mounted laser aimed at Atlas HQ, and he's threatening to slice me in half unless I surrender! I'm, uh, freaking out, here. Freaking out! Oh, and Zer0 reports the laser's being powered by a Vault Key fragment, so, uh...
Ooh, ooh, idea. Um. Shut down that stabilizing thruster. Might buy us some time!
I will never forgive Katagawa for destroying Lazy River Land. I used to take my team there to unwind! And now I'm wound! And all out of bagels!
Come on, Vault Hunter. We got lasers to stop!
Find a way to destroy the servers yet, Vault Hunter?
Boo-ya! Thrust that, thrusters!||That sounded better in my head. Disregard. But look, it's working!
Section 35 thrusters malfunctioning.
What the hell is happening? I was just about to give Atlas HQ a mohawk. Get those thrusters up and running now!
Hell yeah. Now clear out those cultists and keep going! The back entrance to the facility is just up ahead!
That chute is your ticket in! All you gotta do is find the release lever!
Clear the room, Vault Hunter! That laser is OURS!
Come talk to me on the bridge.

You're putting Maliwan to shame out there, killer. Thanks to you, Atlas might just survive this war after all. But we can't lose sight of the Vault. We gotta get there before the Calypsos. That's our mission.
Looks like your Vault Hunters are still scuttling about. You just won't give up, will you, Rhys? That's it. Say goodbye to your favorite frogurt stand!
Not Fran's Fro-gurts. A-Anything but Fran's Frogurts. I mean, t-t-t-t-they give you t-t-that—
—fresh fruit... on the, in the, on the... on the bot—on the bottom, oh my god... Ohhh GOD!
Security! They're in the laser control room—destroy them immediately!
I'm in!
Rhys... Rhys, don't do this. Do not do this, Rhys, I swear... if you fire that laser, we're done, buddy. We are done!
All right. Now that fragment's yours for the taking.
Not so fast, Rhys...
Nice save, Rhys.
We will, Firehawk.

Are you bloody seeing this? It was bad enough with the ground invasion and the warships looming overhead. Now they're just burning off pieces of the city from bloody space? I hate this stupid war. I want to go back to serving lattes.
So... the tattoos. You wanna talk about it?
Honestly, no. Not much to say.
Gotcha. Well, I should probably get settled in. It's good to be back on Sanctuary. A Sanctuary.

Ugh, I can't believe Katagawa destroyed my ship! Just—I just, I just want Atlas to be a real corporation again. You were such a part of that, my sweet invisible Adonis. I should have kept you safer. No, I've got to be strong now. For both of us! Rest in peace. You will be avenged!
Ta-da! What, nothing? Come on, I just got you into a freaking Maliwan base. A little celebration's in order. Just press the celebration button. Think it's Q.
Ugh, whatever. Head on in! The laser control room awaits!
All right! You know what to do.
